# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-59084
# Product:   apache tomcat
# Tags:      [RCE] [CRIT] [T1] [WIDE]
# Score:     100
# Tier:      CRITICAL — ACT NOW
# Generated: 2026-07-21T04:20:13.092765Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only. The vulnerability is described as an insufficient
# documentation issue for EncryptInterceptor in Apache Tomcat, where
# misconfiguration of cluster encryption settings may enable network
# exploitation [1][3]. No specific exploit payload structure, protocol
# framing, or wire-format detail is available from the advisory [2][3],
# making it impossible to construct a high-fidelity content match.
# The rule below targets Tomcat cluster replication traffic (default port
# 4001/tcp, used by SimpleTcpCluster/EncryptInterceptor) and flags
# unencrypted or plaintext-looking cluster messages, which would be
# observable when EncryptInterceptor is absent or misconfigured. This
# is a low-confidence heuristic only.
# PoC status: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the
# CVE/advisory description only.
# PCAP status: No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to
# this pipeline — this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit
# traffic.
# SEVERITY NOTE: CVE-2026-59084 carries a CVSS score of 9.1 (CRITICAL) [1]
# with network-exploitable RCE attributed (AV:N/PR:N/UI:N). Analysts
# should review whether the CRITICAL rating is appropriate for a
# documentation/misconfiguration class vulnerability before tuning
# response actions. The advisory [2][3] indicates exploit requires user
# misconfiguration of EncryptInterceptor — this context must inform
# deployment decisions for this rule.
# THIS RULE IS A PROPOSED DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW. Validate and tune
# before deployment in any blocking/IPS mode.
alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET 4001 (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-59084 Apache Tomcat EncryptInterceptor misconfiguration cluster traffic attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  dsize:>0;
  content:"BackupManager";
  nocase;
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 3, seconds 10;
  reference:cve,2026-59084;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:policy-violation;
  sid:9000084; rev:1; )

